# Coverage thresholds

## Global thresholds (backstop)

Configured in root `vitest.config.ts` as a backstop only:

| Metric | Threshold | Enforcement |
|--------|-----------|-------------|
| Lines | 80% | Hard fail in CI |
| Statements | 80% | Hard fail in CI |
| Functions | 70% | Hard fail in CI |
| Branches | 75% | Hard fail in CI |

## Per-package thresholds (authoritative gate)

Run by `pnpm run test:coverage`, which executes `scripts/per-package-coverage.mjs`.
Each public package is gated by its **own** ratcheted floor in
`scripts/coverage-policy.json`, so a weakly tested package can no longer pass
CI on the back of coverage from other workspaces (ALP-23).

- Floors are ratcheted from the current per-package Vitest coverage
  (`actual - 1`, minimum 40%). Packages at/above a global default keep that
  default.
- Raise a floor (improve the bar) by editing `scripts/coverage-policy.json`.
- Lowering a floor requires justification and must stay ≥ the 40% minimum.
- Packages below the minimum need a documented `exempt` entry (with a
  justification string) in `scripts/coverage-policy.json` — see ALP-23
  acceptance criteria. `repo:check` validates these.
- New public packages MUST declare a floor (or `exempt`) before merge.

## Per-package expectations

| Package type | Key coverage area |
|-------------|-------------------|
| Store plugins | Store initialization, state mutations, method calls, cross-store interactions |
| Magic plugins | Return value correctness, SSR safety, option normalization |
| Headless controllers | State machine transitions, event emission, cleanup |
| Query adapters | Reactivity bridge, stale handling, GC |

## Enforcement

```bash
pnpm run test:coverage            # per-package gate (CI)
pnpm run test:coverage:global     # global backstop only
node scripts/per-package-coverage.mjs --threshold-only   # validate policy entries
```

## Rules

- Every behavior change MUST include tests.
- Global thresholds MUST NOT be lowered.
- New packages MUST meet minimum thresholds before first publish.
- Coverage exclusions MUST be documented in `vitest.config.ts` with rationale.
